<p> Nowcast was founded in San Francisco, during the beginning of the COVID19 plague and lockdown in early 2020. As we all tried to adjust to the new reality of <a target=_blank href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fbflT6G9DMs'>having to stay apart</a>, we decided to do what we can to stay connected with our friends and family both locally and around the world, do what we can to help those hit the hardest economically continue their work online, and help us all observe social distancing so we can stay healthy both physically and emotionally.</p>

<p> We are huge fans of San Francisco. If we were more musically talented, we'd write songs about it, like Scott McKenzie's beautiful song about <a target=_blank href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bch1_Ep5M1s'>wearing flowers in your hair</a>. Until then, we built a platform for like-minded people who can do cool or valuable things over live video to connect with those that want or need it. We're all in this together, and if we can't be physically together, we can at least do it online.</p>

